   <li>Final device status (returned to service or sent for repair)</li>
 </ul>
 
-<h3>Final Thought</h3>
+<h2>Final Thought</h2>
 <p>Pad and therapy cable issues are common, external, and often simple to resolve. A structured approach ensures you rule out connection and consumable problems before escalating to internal failure.</p>
 
 <p>Effective troubleshooting means:</p>
 <ul>
   <li>Prioritizing patient safety</li>
   <li>Verifying simple causes first</li>
   <li>Isolating components logically</li>
   <li>Escalating appropriately</li>
   <li>Documenting clearly</li>
 </ul>
 
 <p><strong>That is successful troubleshooting.</strong></p>
 
